summary: Episode 419 – Mikhaila Peterson – Carnivore Diet Advanced Blood Work
title: Episode 419 – Mikhaila Peterson – Carnivore Diet Advanced Blood Work
body:
This episode of the podcast we have guest Mikhaila Peterson. Mikhaila has become well known for putting her severe Rheumatoid Arthritis into remission by using a carnivore diet after trying everything else.

Listen in as we chat about the carnivore diet and the results of her new blood work she had done recently.

Show Notes

[0:53] – Summary and pre-intro
[2:18] – Introduction, and Mikhaila’s previous carnivore bloodwork
[3:15] – Last ditch effort to manage autoimmune disease (RA)
[3:50] – Pregnancy affecting autoimmune disease
[6:50] – Inventing the autoimmune paleo diet protocol
[9:08] – How the carnivore diet got on Mikhaila’s radar
[15:50] – Mikhaila’s first round of blood work on carnivore
[17:38] – Advanced testing blood work results (second round)
[24:50] – Mikhaila’s takeaway from her recent bloodwork
[27:40] – Robb’s great experience with loperamide (Imodium)
[31:14] – How people are doing the carnivore diet
[33:11] – Paleomedicina experience in Hungary
[35:15] – Case studies reversing Type-1 diabetes when caught early
[40:0] – Robb’s 6-week carnivore diet experience
[45:30] – What Mikhaila has coming up

Link to first round of blood work on Carnivore: http://mikhailapeterson.com/2018/08/07/blood-work/

Mikhaila’s second round of blood work on Carnivore (more advanced): PDF Download

Is the carnivore diet for you? If you want to learn more: check out our Carnivore Diet 101 guide

Transcript:

Coming soon…..

The keto diet is one of the most effective ways to shed fat and improve your health. Keto Masterclass helps you start keto right, step-by-step, so that you can be successful long-term.

body:

Today, the increase in the burden of diseases has increased the demands of health care professionals in particular Nurses who are the key assets to these agencies. Unfortunately, there is a huge difference between the numbers of nurses between developed and developing countries. Various databases were used to identify this gap, rationales behind its existence and recommendations to improve it. For More Information,

if you could see me now
summary:
Dear universe, quit being a jack ass. 
So far.... Lilith didn’t sleep, she had a shot yesterday, so I’m assuming that’s the...
body:
Dear universe, quit being a jack ass.

So far…. Lilith didn’t sleep, she had a shot yesterday, so I’m assuming that’s the culprit, but honestly, it’s not like she sleeps a solid 8 hours a night anyways, just random snippets. While she was asleep, my son woke up and was bawling, hauled him into bed with us where he was talking in his sleep, which rouses me just enough to keep from getting into a fitful rest.

Around 3 am, I got up with the baby, to step in a pile of cold, congealed, dog vomit. Two thumbs up!!! Which had me debating, is it worse to step in cold dog vomit or hot vomit? I say cold, what say you?

I go to drop the baby and the door locks for the daycare are malfunctioning, so I couldn’t drop Lilith on time, and had to wait for security to reboot the system before I or the staff could get into the building. THEN I get to my designated parking lot across campus and half of it is roped off, which forces me to park in some obscure faraway land. I finally get into my office, and someone used my desk and moved all my things, changed my chair, took my lab coat….. I ge gif someone needs to use my space, for real though, when I need to do the same, I try to leave things as I found them. I sort a few necessities, turn on my computer, the system wants me to change my password. Which I do, then the computer shuts down. In the middle of it.

So sincerely universe, I got the message, we’re not cool. I’ll try to sing you some kumbaya when I get home tonight xx
